 Sotheby's Logo
Sotheby’s is a British-founded American multinational corporation headquartered in New York City. It is one of the world’s largest brokers of fine and decorative art, jewelry, and collectibles. It has 80 locations in 40 countries, but maintains a significant presence in the UK. Sotheby’s Institute of Art, Sotheby’s International Realty, and RM Sotheby’s are subsidiaries or partner organisations. Sotheby’s was established on 11 March 1744 in London by Samuel Baker, a bookseller.
